# Current feature

## Status

In progress

## Goals

- Implement `.cursor/features/auth-phase-1-spec.md` (NextAuth v5 + GitHub OAuth)
- Use Prisma adapter with split config pattern for edge compatibility
- Protect `/dashboard/*` routes via `src/proxy.ts` redirecting unauthenticated users to sign-in

## Notes

- **Overview**: Set up NextAuth v5 with Prisma adapter and GitHub OAuth. Use NextAuth default pages for testing.
- **Files to create**:
  - `src/auth.config.ts` (edge-compatible providers only; no adapter)
  - `src/auth.ts` (full config + Prisma adapter; session strategy `jwt`)
  - `src/app/api/auth/[...nextauth]/route.ts` (export handlers from `src/auth.ts`)
  - `src/proxy.ts` (route protection + redirect logic)
  - `src/types/next-auth.d.ts` (extend Session with `user.id`)
- **Environment variables**:
  - `AUTH_SECRET`
  - `AUTH_GITHUB_ID`
  - `AUTH_GITHUB_SECRET`
- **Testing checklist**:
  - Visit `/dashboard` → redirects to sign-in
  - Sign in with GitHub → redirects back to `/dashboard`

